snippet.textDisplay:
No a mortgage company will not touch this but it's also only 14,000 pounds. People take out private loans on 14,000 pound items all the time that oftern have higher maintenance than this little house things like a new car for example or a caravan. Many loan companies and banks will loan you 14k even if they do not call it a mortgage. Also if you are looking at living in this then it doesn't take a math genius to work out that 4.24% (standard home loan variable in the UK) of 300,000 over 30 years is far more interest than 8.2% (avarge interest on a secured personal loan in the UK) over 5 - 8 years.

On a personal note I do not live in the UK I live in Australia and we are Nazis when it comes to permits when building anything. In 2012 I built a shed that fits one car on my mother's property because the shed had a concrete slab I had to pay out for a permit that cost more than the shed itself. This little house would require a building permit and I wonder if this would even be allowed or able to get a permit.
